<div class="section">
    <h1>uniformThumb</h1>
    <p class="margin-v">
        The size of the image doesn't matter, it will fill the shape of the <code>.uniformThumb</code> using <code>object-fit: cover;</code>.
    </p>
    <p class="margin-v">
        <code>.uniformThumb</code> requires a width and height to be set because it cannot rely on the dimensions of the image. Fortunately, using the <code>aspect-</code> utility only the width dimension has to be explicit.
    </p>
    
<% thumb = capture_html do %>
<div class="uniformThumb :selector">
    <img src="https://unsplash.it/200/200/?random" width="200" height="200">
</div>
<% end %>

    
    <h3><code>.uniformThumb.aspect-square</code></h3>
    <div class="flex space-h">
        <div class="width-1/2">
            <%= thumb.gsub(":selector", "width-100-px aspect-square") %>
        </div>
        <div class="width-1/2">
            <% code 'html' do %>
                <%= thumb.gsub(":selector", "width-100-px aspect-square") %>
            <% end %>
        </div>
    </div>
    
